          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\"drivers/ata/libata-core.c\"],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\"ata_device_blacklist\"],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"Samsung 860 EVO SSD is missing from the ata_device_blacklist[] array in libata-core.c. The device causes queued TRIM timeouts because it is not listed with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag. Similar Samsung SSDs (840 and 850 series) are already in the blacklist with this flag at lines 4562-4565. The fix requires adding a new entry: { \\\"Samsung SSD 860*\\\", NULL, ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM | ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM }. The horkage flag is applied at line 2477 (dev->horkage |= ata_dev_blacklisted(dev)) and checked in ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() function at line 2218 to disable queued TRIM for affected devices.\"\n}\n",
